sec.p:
Leg volume (V) was calculated by measuring ankle and maximal calf diameters with a tape measure, the vertical distance between the two points (h), deriving ankle and calf radii (R1 and R2), and applying a truncated inverted cone model.20 This was performed bilaterally.




